


@{ViewBag.Title = "Central line improvement works at east end of the line";}
        
        

<div class="r">
    <div class="headline-container plain">
        <h1>Central line improvement works at east end of the line</h1>
        <div class="content-page-press-release">
        04 October 2005
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="main-and-aside r">
    <div class="main" role="main">

    <div class="article-teaser">
        Buses will replace trains between Woodford and Epping and between Hainault and Woodford during the following weekends: 8-9 October, 12-13 November, 3-4 December due to station refurbishment works at Loughton, Theydon Bois and Epping, as well as track replacement taking place at Roding Valley.
        
    </div>



 <div class="on-this-page">
<div class="pullquote right">
                        <p>
                            Customers are advised to allow an extra 30 minutes to complete their journey
                            
                        </p>
                    </div>
                
            
            
            <p>Works are part of TfL's 5-year &pound;10bn investment programme and will be undertaken by Metronet Rail BCV.</p>
<p>Three Rail Replacement Bus services will operate:<br><strong>A:</strong> Between Woodford and Epping; <br><strong>B:</strong> Between Epping and Theydon Bois<br><strong>C:</strong> Between Hainault and Woodford</p>
<p>Customers are advised to allow an extra 30 minutes to complete their journey, especially those wishing to make the last train connections.</p>
<p>Passengers travelling from/to the listed stations are advised to use the following routes:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Theydon Bois:</strong> Travel via Epping</li>
<li><strong>Stations east of Woodford:</strong> Rail Replacement bus service</li>
<li><strong>Between Hainault and Woodford:</strong> Rail Replacement Bus Service</li>
<li><strong>Grange Hill:</strong> Travel via Hainault</li>
<li><strong>Chigwell/Roding Valley</strong>: Travel via Woodford</li></ul>
<hr>

<p>For 24-hour information on public transport in London, please call: 020 7222 1234.<br><br>TfL's Realtime pages display live travel information on London's public transport network: <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/realtime">www.tfl.gov.uk/realtime</a> </p>
<p>Journey Planner checks the transport network's status before providing results. The best available route is shown automatically: <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/journeyplanner">www.tfl.gov.uk/journeyplanner</a> </p>
<p>Travel alerts via SMS and email can be set up at: <a href="http://www.tfl.gov.uk/alerts">www.tfl.gov.uk/alerts</a></p>
            <ul>
<li>TfL is investing &pound;10bn over the next five years to improve and expand London's transport network, over half of that in the Tube</li>
<li>Metronet Rail BCV is responsible for the maintenance and renewal of the Bakerloo, Central, Victoria and Waterloo &amp; City lines</li>
<li>The Central line is the longest line, with 74km (46 miles) serving 49 stations</li>
<li>The longest journey without change on the London Underground can be made on the Central line between West Ruislip and Epping (54.9 km, 34.1 miles)<br></li></ul>

     

        
        
        
